<TEXT>
when thousands of indians stood and sang 
born in the usa they werent having an identify crisis 
they were singing with bruce springsteen during an eighthour 
rock concert friday night celebrating the 40th anniversary of the 
united nations universal declaration on human rights 
it was the first live western rock concert to be staged in india 
in nearly eight years the last group to appear was boney m in 1980 
the sellout crowd of 55000 fans including prime minister 
rajiv gandhis two teenage children filled nehru stadium to 
listen to springsteen sting peter gabriel tracy chapman the 
epidemics and youssou dnour and their appeals on behalf of amesty 
international the londonbased human rights organization 
the concert was part of amnestys 23 million extravaganza 
scheduled to travel to 20 countries on five continents the tour 
runs through oct 15 with the finale scheduled in buenos aires 
argentina 
shortly after the show began about 30 news photographers walked 
out after a scuffle between a colleague and a security official 
sondeep shankar a photographer for the times of india 
newspaper said he was assaulted when security men asked him to 
leave the pit below the stage 
a concert official speaking on condition of anonymity claimed 
the photographer began violent and abusive 
few in the crowd were aware of the boycott 
i came to see springsteen said hitiesh ahuja an 
18yearold high school student whose ticket cost about 8 dollars 
we cant believe hes really here 
prior to friday nights show concert organizations complained 
the times of india which sponsored the show had been promoting 
its 150th anniversary rather than human rights 
we didnt come here to celebrate anybodys birthday bash 
springsteen told a news conference 
other performers were upset that some tickets cost as much as 
140 about half the average annual income in india 
we are here to reach out to the common people of india and 
raise their consciousness about the importance of human rights that 
are violated all over the world the show is not to raise money 
gabriel said 
</TEXT>
