<TEXT>
george bush has struck again at 
democrat michael dukakis home turf a tactic aides say will 
continue as the republican campaign tries to keep the massachusetts 
governor on the defensive 
in a campaign stop kept secret until just a few hours before 
bush on friday scooted to springfield in central massachusetts to 
receive endorsements from local law enforcement groups it was just 
eight days after bush blasted into boston to get the nod from the 
police union there 
the endorsement comes from you who know the truth not just 
about me but about my opponent as well bush said thanking the 
local branch of the international brotherhood of police officers 
and the springfield police department supervisors association 
officer robert jacobson president of the ibpo local said his 
group decided to endorse bush because of his support of the death 
penalty and because of the prison furlough program that dukakis had 
supported 
our members have never supported furloughs for firstdegree 
murderers but michael dukakis did he said until public 
opinion drove him to change his mind they continued 
the program has since been altered to exclude firstdegree 
murderers 
ron kaufman the northeast regional coordinator for the bush 
campaign said the efforts to embarrass dukakis on his home turf 
would continue 
bushs first public events were in new jersey where he also 
received the endorsement of local police groups 
bush was introduced in paterson by passaic county sheriff edwin 
englehardt who chopped at the american civil liberties union its 
a group bush frequently attacks and dares dukakis to quit 
the paterson officers he said dont want a man in that white 
house who is a sympathizer and a cardcarrying member of the aclu 
that great organization thats against everything thats right for 
america 
bush then repeated his blast of dukakis as an aclu member 
dukakis supported the basic revolvingdoor program for 
murderers while he by contrast wanted murders executed bush 
said 
my opponent had the nerve yesterday to come in here and talk 
about oceans you cant swim in bush said you tried to drink 
the water in boston harbor recently dont do it he was 
referring to pollution and not to the brine content of boston 
harbors sea water 
from the paterson municipal center bush went to nearby 
ridgefield memorial high school where he barely mentioned the 
campaign in a softspoken appeal to the students to fight drug use 
bush then returned to the attack in springfield mass where he 
also declared i am running as myself and my opponent is running 
from himself 
he then paid a courtesy call on archbishop john whealon in 
hartford conn and finished the trip with a rally in west 
hartford bush renewed the attack on an array of issues including 
crime and dukakis plan to crack down on tax cheats 
it was wrong to hire three divisions of irs agents to go 
into every kitchen in america looking for people who havent 
paid their fair share of taxes he said 
in washington bush spokesman steve hart disputed a statement by 
former central intelligence agency director stansfield turner that 
bush rehired panamanian leader manuel antonio noriega as a cia 
source in 1981 
turner told several news organizations that he had fired 
noriega the head of panamas military and de facto ruler of the 
country in 1976 because noriega was an unscrupulous character 
the dukakis campaign has made an issue of the reagan 
administrations dealings with noriega up until his recent 
indictment in the united states on drug charges 
the vice president had no public events scheduled today or 
sunday he planned to resume campaigning monday with a trip to 
california to watch the return of the space shuttle 
