the house ethics committee apparently has 
begun an informal investigation into whether speaker jim wright 
violated rules against disclosing government secrets when he talked 
openly last week about a purported cia covert operation in 
nicaragua 
on friday the ethics panel asked the house intelligence 
committee to notify it whether wright had been given access to 
classified information from the spy agency on its activities in the 
region 
the senior republican on the intelligence committee rep henry 
hyde of illinois said he was confident the panel would cooperate 
with the request for information even though it declined earlier 
this week to send such information to ethics 
the ethics committees request came as gop members of the 
intelligence committee said they were prepared to ask the full 
house to investigate wright if action were not forthcoming soon 
democrats responded angrily to that announcement charging that 
the move was motivated by politics and by frustrations of contra 
