<TEXT>
congress racing against the clock completed 
work friday on the last of 13 spending bills just three minutes 
before the start of the new fiscal year even as president reagan 
chided lawmakers for the dogatemyhomework era of congressional 
budgetry 
it was the first time since 1976 that congress had passed all 13 
separate spending bills 
senate majority leader robert byrd dwva said the lawmakers 
accomplishment on the fiscal 1989 spending bills renewed faith 
and confidence in this institution 
at 1157 pm senators accepted by voice vote house language on 
a 143 billion foreign aid measure finishing a marathon day in 
which congress cleared five appropriations bills for fiscal 1989 
two minutes later a puffing house clerk ran into the senate 
chamber carrying the house legislation technically sealing the 
agreement reached by the vote minutes earlier 
fiscal 1988 ended at midnight 
reagan had planned to hold a latenight signing ceremony at the 
white house for the final spending measures but with congress 
still working he canceled the ceremony and instead issued a 
statement complaining about the dogatemyhomework era of 
congressional budgetry 
white house spokesman bill harlow said reagan would have no 
comment on the final passage of all 13 bills until saturday 
had reagan signed the bills before midnight it would have 
marked the first time since 1948 that all 13 spending measures were 
enacted before the start of the fiscal year 
since that time the budget process has been marked by squabbles 
that have resulted in some or all of the spending measures being 
wrapped together that practice rankles presidents because as the 
bills grow to cover more and more federal agencies the political 
consequences of a veto become more serious 
even though the fiscal year opened saturday without the 
presidents signature on six of the bills the effect will be 
almost nil 
few federal employees work over the weekend and even without 
spending legislation in place essential workers would report 
including the military doctors air traffic controllers and 
others but if all the spending bills are not enacted by monday 
agencies for which money has not been provided would not be able to 
keep their doors open 
the house opened business friday by approving a 282 billion 
defense department spending measure on a 32777 vote and sent it to 
the senate the senate later approved it but added some provisions 
which sent the bill back to the house as both chambers must 
approve identical bills the house concurred with the changes 
the senate also voted 904 in favor of a houseapproved 466 
billion agriculture bill and sent it to reagan 
all told reagan has signed seven fiscal 1989 appropriations 
bills into law most recently the 108 billion transportation bill 
on friday the first was a 178 billion measure for energy and 
water projects enacted on july 19 
as the midnight deadline approached friday the senate gave 
final approval to a 32 billion district of columbia 
appropriations bill that carried a strong antiabortion amendment 
and gave georgetown university the right to deny certain rights to 
gay groups 
dc delegate walter fauntroy angered by the intrusion into 
local affairs said he would encourage city officials to disobey 
the abortionfunding prohibition to trigger a congressionally 
mandated shutdown of city government such a move would leave 
congress with the responsibility of governing the nations capital 
the federal government contributes 537 million to the dc 
government 
as the clock ticked on legislation providing 18 billion for 
congress own operating expenses received final approval that left 
the 143 billion foreign aid measure 
the uncharacteristic rapidity with which the spending measures 
were being completed this year is largely due to last novembers 
budget summit agreement between reagan and congressional leaders 
that pact set the broad spending targets for 1989 and set a tone 
in which administration and capitol hill officials consulted 
frequently in an effort to resolve disputes 
it shows what can happen when the president and congress 
cooperate byrd said 
last years budget process produced nothing but partisan 
brawling over spending levels and taxes with neither the 
administration nor congress willing to budge the beginning of 
fiscal 1988 came and went without the passage of a single 
appropriations bill 
what emerged and not until late december three months into 
the fiscal year was a 1400page 600 billion measure wrapping 
all 13 spending bills into one 
reagan signed the measure but in january he promised on 
national television to never again sign an omnibus spending bill 
and scores of lawmakers pledged to send the bills to the white 
house one at a time 
