<TEXT>
here are some basic facts about kosmos 1900 
the soviet spy satellite expected to fall to earth soon based on 
information provided by the us and canadian governments 
type kosmos 1900 is a soviet rorsat ocean reconnaissance 
satellite powered by a nuclear reactor like two others which have 
fallen to earth kosmos 954 in 1978 which dropped on remote 
northwest canada and kosmos 1402 which splashed into the indian 
ocean in 1983 
size western experts estimate the weight of kosmos 1900 at 
about 2200 pounds and its dimensions about 20 feet by 7 feet 
reactor the satellite carries a nuclear reactor estimated to 
weigh about 220 pounds and fueled by an estimated 110 pounds of 
uranium u235 much of which will have degraded to radioactive 
isotopes 
odds the satellite has been falling slowly from orbit since 
april when the soviets lost radio communications with it the 
chances are 66 percent that it will land in water 33 percent on 
land 5 percent in the united states 3 percent in canada and 1 
percent onto a populated area 
fallout if the reactor ejects on reentry as planned the 
radioactive material will turn to dust and settle slowly from the 
atmosphere posing little danger if the reactor reenters the 
atmosphere protected by the satellite the radioactive bits 
probably would be about the same size as those from kosmos 954 
experts recovered 3000 such pieces most less than a millimeter 
long or 04 inches with a few 500 to 700 milimeters long 20 to 
28 inches according to canadian officials 
danger humans face danger from exposure to gamma radiation from 
highly radioactive material the larger the radioactive piece the 
greater the danger 
precautions listen for official warnings carried by the media 
stay indoors if authorities warn that the satellite will be falling 
in your area do not touch or remain in the vicinity of strange 
objects if you come into contact with such objects remove 
contaminated clothes place them in a plastic bag shower and call 
the authorities 
reimbursement the soviet government repaid canada one half the 
35 million required to clean up material from kosmos 954 canada 
did not seek compensation for environmental damages 
</TEXT>
