<TEXT>
commander frederick h hauck today 
took time out from the discovery crews schedule to read a letter 
from a new york teenager who said he was worried about the 
future and assured the boy that america is back on track 
in the letter sent to hauck before the launch pj morgan of 
brooklyn said 
dear mr hauck im a worried 14yearold that is worried 
about the future i feel that some of americas future is riding on 
you and your crews shoulders i give you all the inspiration i can 
give you because your ride this fall means so much to me 
hauck said he received the letter within the last year and a 
half and called the boy just before the launch 
i thought it was a particularly good letter and really sent 
home to us how much the experiences we have here in space can have 
an effect on the youngsters of america hauck said 
hauck said morgan told him he had been inspired by his science 
teacher at st marks parochial school in brooklyn because he had 
some concerns about the future of america and whether we were still 
capable of doing the things that make us a great country 
the mission commander thanked the boy for the letter and said he 
hoped all the other youngsters out there not only in america but 
in other parts of the world that may be watching and can see that 
we are back on track and we have a lot of technological benefits 
that will come in the future 
the mission commander read the letter just after astronaut john 
