here is the text of andrei a gromykos farewell 
speech to saturdays session of the supreme soviet which replaced 
him as soviet president the speech was translated by the 
associated press 
i would like to express my gratitude to the general secretary of 
the central committee of the communist party mikhail sergeyevich 
gorbachev for everything he said yesterday at the plenum of the 
central committee while addressing me for the evaluation of my 
work which included my work as chairman of the presidium of the 
supreme soviet the central committee plenum supported my request 
to resign due to age 
what else can i say my work is wellknown nearly all the 
time starting with my appointment to the diplomatic service this 
work has been conducted in full view the length of my service is 
nearly half a century i express deep gratitude to you comrade 
deputies for our work together in these first years of the great 
restructuring 
all our people the party of communists are busy with the 
implementation of grandiose plans new tasks arise and the elected 
representatives of the people the deputies must take on the 
modernization of the political system the completion of the 
creation of the social and legal state it will demand tremendous 
effort but the communist party and its central committee are fully 
determined to fulfill the daring and wellfounded program for the 
countrys development 
the enrichment of soviet democracy and openness is a mighty 
source for the soviet people to derive strength for new 
achievements both in domestic life and for the implementation of 
the leninist peace policy in international affairs 
i believe in the tremendous strength of our ideas and 
principles armed with this belief our people traversed the 
difficult but heroic path after the great october revolution we 
all know what sacrificies were made at various stages of history of 
the soviet state but our land of socialism not only survived but 
gained the power to move forward with a sure step 
yes in the history of our country there have been failures 
they are wellknown we justly and surely condemn them but the 
star of socialism has been shining brightly ever since october 
1917 it was kindled in the land of the soviets never to be dimmed 
people today expect the soviets on all levels to contribute to 
perestroika such a contribution is worthy of the grandiose plans 
set by the party 
experience shows that for solving the great tasks that confront 
the country our leninist party needs not only a clear head and 
sturdy shoulders but unity in its ranks as well this necessity has 
been proved by our history since october the unity of the party 
its unity with the people are as necessary for solving our great 
tasks as air is to a human being we have this unity in the central 
committee as well as in the politburo 
surveying our great country i would like to share a feeling 
that is constantly with me confidence in tomorrow what gives me 
this confidence first of all the remarkable people living in the 
country who can solve the most complicated problems second we 
have a wise and sagacious party closely linked to the people 
third the leadership that has been consolidated is worthy of the 
great tasks the country faces at this turning point in the 
development of soviet society and at this turning point in the 
development of the international situation 
the party and country together with other fraternal parties and 
countries will continue the tireless struggle for peace among 
nations this is our main task the essence of our life and of the 
lives of our children and grandchildren 
thank you comrade deputies for the trust you have given me 
i appreciated and appreciate this trust 
</TEXT>
