a small earthquake beneath the san gabriel 
mountains shook parts of the san fernando valley on saturday the 
first anniversary of a deadly temblor that caused millions of 
dollars in damage in los angeles county 
the 1056 am earthquake measured 35 on the richter scale 
said robert finn spokesman for the california institute of 
technology in pasadena 
the earthquake occurred on a different fault than the 
destructive oct 1 1987 whittier quake and was unrelated finn 
said 
seismologists pinpointed the quakes epicenter at 19 miles north 
of downtown about five miles northwest of the sunland district 
the location is in angeles national forest under the south slope of 
the san gabriels 
the 1987 earthquake was centered in whittier narrows southeast 
of los angeles it measured 59 on the scale and was followed by a 
53magnitude oct 4 aftershock the two quakes caused eight 
deaths 200 injuries and 358 million in damage 
an earthquake measuring 35 can cause slight damage in the local 
area quakes measuring 5 and 6 can cause considerable to severe 
damage 
residents and workers in the vicinity of saturdays quake did 
not report any damage 
