fledgling tropical storm isaac lost its punch 
saturday and was downgraded to a depression then a tropical wave 
prompting cancellations of storm warnings for six caribbean islands 
isaac which formed friday in the tropical atlantic just as 
hurricane helene was reclassified as a bad storm in the far north 
atlantic was clipped by strong winds in the upper atmosphere 
those winds scattered isaacs strength 
at 6 pm edt isaac was classified a tropical wave after losing 
its surface circulation at noon it was located about 770 miles 
southeast of portauprince haiti the wave was moving toward the 
west away from the windward islands said forecasters at the 
national hurricane center 
but forecaster bob case said showers and thunderstorms could 
dump heavy rains on parts of the windward islands through saturday 
night he advised small craft in the lesser antilles to remain in 
port until winds and seas subside 
when isaac weakened tropical storm warnings were canceled for 
the islands of barbados the grenadines st vincent st lucia 
dominica and martinique trinidad and tobago discontinued tropical 
storm watches earlier saturday 
also saturday forecasters were watching a westwardmoving 
tropical wave in the atlantic midway between northwestern africa 
and the lesser antilles 
tropical waves become depressions if winds start moving in a 
circular pattern around cores of low pressure they become named 
storms if winds hit 39 mph and hurricanes if winds reach 74 mph 
isaac was the ninth named storm of the sixmonth atlantic hurricane 
season which started june 1 
