emperor hirohito received a blood transfusion after 
suffering more internal bleeding sunday but doctors said the 
87yearold monarchs condition was stable 
the tranfusion was the second since hirohitos condition 
suddenly deteriorated saturday when worsening internal bleeding 
caused his blood pressure to plummet 
relatives rushed to his bedside but his condition stabilized 
after a transfusion on saturday doctors said 
the imperial household agency said that the emperor was given 
another 04pint transfusion sunday after discharging a small 
amount of blood through his bowels 
the palace reported that as of 900 am 8 pm edt the 
