<TEXT>
actress helen mirren like thousands of 
britons before her traveled to the seaside spa of bournemouth to 
inspect the little cottage where the murder took place 53 years ago 
mirrens visit to the house beside the english channel was 
different from those of the merely curious she was researching her 
role as accused murderess alma rattenbury in cause celebre 
which can be seen on pbs mystery in two parts thursday and 
oct 20 
rattenbury 38 was accused along with her teenage lover 
george bowman of bludgeoning her elderly husband to death in 1935 
their trial in londons old bailey caused a sensation and 
rattenbury was widely reviled in england 
i went to the house and i could feel the terrible trauma the 
people felt said mirren the house hasnt changed its 
character since the tragedy took place bournemouth is a very 
middle class bourgeois narrowminded smug town 
ever since the little house in bournemouth has drawn the 
curious who still seek out the house and visit the cemetery in 
search of the unmarked graves 
francis rattenbury is buried apart from his wife she was 
acquitted of the charge of murder but within days stabbed herself 
four times in the heart bowman was sentenced to death but the 
sentence was commuted to life imprisonment he served seven years 
bowman now 72 still lives in bournemouth 
i think i feel more strongly about cause celebre than any 
other piece of work ive done said mirren she has starred in 
such movies as white nights excalibur age of consent 
the mosquito coast 2010 the fiendish plot of dr fu 
