<TEXT>
comparison shopping for an auto insurer can result in 
sharply reduced insurance costs 
while all auto insurance policies may appear similar quite 
the opposite is true says charles f wright assistant vice 
president aetna life amp casualty and a smart consumer can often 
save hundreds of dollars 
some of the moneysaving discounts offered by various companies 
he says include 
a total account credit to those who insure both car and 
home with the same company the credit differs from state to state 
wright says but is usually 10 percent off the auto premium or 5 
percent off both auto and homeowner premiums 
some companies offer a first accident forgiveness which 
after five continous accidentfree years guarantees that rates 
will not go up after a first atfault accident 
car pool commuters often qualify for discounts 
installing antitheft devices in your car may qualify you for 
a discount a 5 percent credit is typical for an alarmonly 
device or an active disabling mechanism which prevents the car from 
starting says wright some companies offer a 10 percent credit 
for a passive disabling device that automatically prevents the car 
from starting 
